{"type": "article", "id": 23089, "title": "一个寻医问药的地方长得像咖啡馆，你会感觉有点怪么？", "description": "是会感觉到放松，还是会怀疑这里不专业？\r\n", "date": "2016-03-01T18:11:29Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 435, "name": "室内设计"}, {"id": 19064, "name": "诊所设计"}], "category": 17, "author": 1329, "comment_count": 1, "praise_count": 86, "image": "img/article/article_show/201606071257454BLEsS62YnbcDaqJ.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p>在设计师眼中，诊所不是冰冷且严肃的，而是有很多种活泼的打开方式。</p>\n<p>比如走清新宜人路线的<a href=\"http://www.qdaily.com/articles/3063.html\">日本住吉堂针灸院</a>和加拿大魁北克一处<a href=\"http://www.qdaily.com/articles/16397.html\">皮肤科诊所</a>，也可以是像西雅图<a href=\"http://www.qdaily.com/articles/15439.html\">私人眼科诊所 Eye Eye</a> 那样的俏皮款，长得像面包店的东京<a href=\"http://www.qdaily.com/articles/17867.html\">家庭式诊所旭町</a>也是个不错的例子。</p>\n<p>总之，设计师们就是喜欢跳出传统医院里沉闷的看诊环境，做一些有利于让病人感到身心放松的设计，这也是时下医院、诊所类项目设计的新趋势。</p>\n<p>最近，在韩国仁川，Design Aram 室内设计团队就带来了诊所设计新作。这间名为「Muse」的诊所彻底打破了医院固有的形象，被构筑成了一个如咖啡馆一般的空间。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-images-wide\">\n<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160607125740a4QC29wqYiLenu5A.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66805556\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201606071257414FPCy7htaNZxVDwp.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.5625\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201606071257411kVzhOdS2e48aw3m.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66805556\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n<p>甚至可以说，设计师还把这两年大肆流行的工业风咖啡馆的设计套路都搬来了 Muse 诊所的空间设计。比如大面积裸露的红砖墙壁与浅灰色混凝土砖墙的对撞，纯黑色钢材与玻璃窗组合创造的看诊室隔离墙，木质格子收纳架上摆放着的各种植物、书籍以及装饰小物件等等，都像是咖啡馆标配。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-images-wide\">\n<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160607125741pSBZy8YJ7AxgPcik.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66805556\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160607125742g8fyXIqHtdCbLkWj.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66805556\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160607125742GX93fm8AvFxEnS2k.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66805556\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160607125743GblSNoPHfYM9dye2.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66805556\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n<p>原木色格栅式样的接待柜台看起来清新温暖，而黑色天花板顶部垂落的黑色圆形吊灯也制造着柔和的室内光线。</p>\n<p>白色、黑色与浅灰色在整个诊所内被大面积运用，但塑造的氛围却并不冰冷，温暖的木质元素穿插运用于柜台、地面、置物架与门窗中，反而带出宜人的味道。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-images-wide\">\n<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160607125743YQWNdFR2ztwx3UE8.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160607125744GjropDkz4BPHEZx9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66805556\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160607125744A31xelTZGqRMcjLE.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160607125745fnMdJ58G4e9tupBW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n<p><a href=\"http://retaildesignblog.net/2016/02/29/muse-clinic-by-design-aram-incheon-south-korea/\">用 Design Aram 团队的话说</a>，这更像是一个为年轻人创造的摩登诊所，来这里不仅是为了看病抓药，也是可以放松休闲的去处。</p>\n<p>图片来自 <a href=\"http://retaildesignblog.net/2016/02/29/muse-clinic-by-design-aram-incheon-south-korea/\">Retail Design Blog</a></p>\n\n\n"}